{{Infobox power station | name = Indian Mesa Wind Farm | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = USA Texas | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|30.9209749|N|102.162771838|W|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | country = United States | location = [[Pecos County, Texas]] | status = | construction_began = | commissioned =2001 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = [[NextEra Energy Resources]] | operator = [[NextEra Energy Resources]] | ps_units_operational = 125 | ps_units_manu_model = [[Vestas]]: V-47 660 kW | wind_hub_height = [[65 meters]] | wind_rotor_diameter = | wind_rated_speed = | wind_farm_type = | wind_site_elevation = | wind_site_usage = | wind_site_area = | wind_offshore_depth = | wind_offshore_distance = | ps_electrical_capacity = 82.5 MW | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | website = https://www.nexteraenergyresources.com/pdf_redesign/Indianmesa.pdf | extra = }} '''Indian Mesa Wind Farm''' is a [[wind farm]] located in [[Pecos County, Texas]]. The farm consists of one hundred twenty-five [[Vestas]] V-47 660 kilowatt wind turbines that produce up to 82.5 megawatts of [[electricity]]. Electricity produced by the project is purchased by the [[Lower Colorado River Authority]] (51 megawatts) and [[Energy Future Holdings Corporation|TXU]] (31.5 megawatts). The project is built on land owned by local ranches and the [[University of Texas]]. The project was completed in 2001 by [[Orion Energy LLC]] and development partner National Wind Power.
[[NextEra_Energy_Resources]] acquired the farm in June, 2002.
