The '''Togo Triangle''' is an offshore market for stolen [[Petroleum|oil]] off the coast of [[Nigeria]] and [[Togo]] near the [[Niger Delta]]. The Triangle has been compared to an "open-air drug market" for trade in illegal crude oil, noted for the presence of pirates.<ref name="NPR_301014">{{cite web |url=https://www.npr.org/blogs/money/2014/10/29/359624435/episode-578-how-to-steal-a-million-barrels-of-oil |title=How To Steal A Million Barrels Of Oil |last1=Smith |first1=Robert |last2=Simon |first2=Julia |date=30 October 2014 |work=[[Planet Money]] |publisher=NPR |accessdate=1 November 2014}}</ref><ref name="Probe_020614">{{cite web |url=http://www.probeng.org/togo-triangle-where-stolen-nigerian-crude-oil-is-sold-2-by-emmanuel-mayah/ |title=Where stolen Nigerian crude oil is sold |last1=Mayah |first1=Emmanuel |date=2 June 2014 |work=Probe |publisher=Wole Soyinka Centre for Investigative Journalism |accessdate=1 November 2014}}</ref>
