The '''Văcăreni Wind Farm''' is a proposed wind power project in [[Văcăreni]], [[Tulcea County]], [[Romania]]. It will have 48 individual [[wind turbine]]s<ref>{{cite web|url=http://standard.money.ro/articol_106936/gica_popescu_intra_in_afacerile_pe_eolian.html|title=Gică Popescu intră în afacerile pe eolian|publisher=''Business Magazin''|language=Romanian|accessdate=2009-09-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091217084956/http://standard.money.ro/articol_106936/gica_popescu_intra_in_afacerile_pe_eolian.html|archive-date=2009-12-17|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> with a nominal output of around 5 [[Watt#Megawatt|MW]] each which will deliver up to 240 MW of power, enough to power over 144,000 homes, with a capital investment required of approximately US$480 million.

